<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-30T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="583" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d583">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.24/349: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico
                                        City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-30T13:00:00-06:00">March 30, 1937—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:13 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>79. The American Consul at Vera Cruz reports that the Spanish ship <hi rend="italic">Motomar</hi> has been loading airplanes from Tejeria
                            Field since March 27th. The <hi rend="italic">Motomar</hi> has left
                            today for Tampico to transport about 500 agrarians and take on oil
                            expecting to return to Vera Cruz to finish loading. All airplanes at
                            Tejeria are reported to be of American manufacture.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>